    public class MXMLDocumentNode
extends MXMLClassDefinitionNode
implements IMXMLDocumentNode
    MXMLDocumentNode represents the root MXML tag in an MXML document.

      • getName

        public String getName()
        Description copied from interface: IMXMLNode
        Gets the name of this node.

        For a node that refers to a class, this is the fully-qualified ActionScript class name. (For example, for <s:Button> it would be "spark.components.Button".)

        For a node that specifies a property, style, or event, this is the name of the property, style, or event. (For example, for <s:text> it would be "text".)

        For a language node, this is the short name of the tag. (For example, for <fx:Script> it would be "Script".)

        Specified by:
        getName in interface IMXMLNode
        Returns:
        The name of this node as a String.

        protected void processChildNonWhitespaceUnit(MXMLTreeBuilder builder,
                                 IMXMLTagData tag,
                                 IMXMLTextData text,
                                 MXMLNodeBase.MXMLNodeInfo info)
        Description copied from class: MXMLNodeBase
        Processes a single child text unit which is not all whitespace.

        The default behavior implemented in this base class is to report each unit of non-whitespace as a problem.

        Subclasses must override this method in order to allow the non-whitespace text unit.

        Overrides:
        processChildNonWhitespaceUnit in class MXMLNodeBase
        text - An MXMLTextData object representing the child text unit.
